272
00:24:03,738 --> 00:24:04,704
for the lesson.

273
00:24:18,624 --> 00:24:21,103
And I really am hurt, you know.
I'm not acting.

274
00:24:21,786 --> 00:24:22,511
I believe you.

275
00:24:22,944 --> 00:24:24,010
With a wound like that,

276
00:24:24,767 --> 00:24:25,918
you should really go to a hospital.

277
00:24:28,835 --> 00:24:29,637
I'll be fine.

278
00:24:30,558 --> 00:24:32,263
Anyway, thank you so much.

279
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:34,378
I'll be going now.

280
00:24:34,586 --> 00:24:35,249
Right.

281
00:24:55,328 --> 00:24:56,371
What?

282
00:25:04,361 --> 00:25:05,184
Officer.

283
00:25:05,466 --> 00:25:07,615
I was really shocked just now.

284
00:25:07,738 --> 00:25:09,161
I just realized that

285
00:25:09,690 --> 00:25:10,781
on my way back,

286
00:25:11,176 --> 00:25:13,948
I might get attacked by my ex-boyfriend.

287
00:25:14,746 --> 00:25:15,530
Oh, dear.

288
00:25:16,122 --> 00:25:17,897
This is just terrible.

289
00:25:18,362 --> 00:25:19,323
Ah.

290
00:25:20,038 --> 00:25:23,158
So, Officer,
could you give me a ride home?

291
00:25:33,370 --> 00:25:38,545
(Thai police are dedicated
to public safety)

292
00:25:40,127 --> 00:25:44,019
"Thai police are dedicated
to public safety."

293
00:25:45,050 --> 00:25:45,870
Right?

294
00:25:51,040 --> 00:25:55,104
(Just Being the Last One
Whom You Think Of)

295
00:25:55,104 --> 00:25:59,392
♪Standing where I never should have been♪

296
00:25:59,392 --> 00:26:03,360
♪And honestly, that's enough for me♪

297
00:26:03,511 --> 00:26:05,008
Why do you do this work?

298
00:26:09,049 --> 00:26:10,166
What work do you mean?

299
00:26:14,333 --> 00:26:15,672
You can stop acting now.

300
00:26:16,783 --> 00:26:17,706
Tell me.

301
00:26:17,944 --> 00:26:20,352
Nothing you say here
will be used as evidence.

302
00:26:28,091 --> 00:26:28,992
Well...

303
00:26:29,526 --> 00:26:30,336
Well...

304
00:26:30,714 --> 00:26:32,748
Truth is, I'm a bar host.

305
00:26:34,074 --> 00:26:37,440
Just came to take
an "entertain" job outside today.

306
00:26:38,239 --> 00:26:39,064
First time.

307
00:26:40,736 --> 00:26:42,080
And as you saw,

308
00:26:42,400 --> 00:26:44,104
I ran straight into that guy.

309
00:26:44,838 --> 00:26:45,744
Oh, Officer.

310
00:26:46,238 --> 00:26:49,727
I'm not a "boy for sale" or anything.
Don't misunderstand.

311
00:26:53,820 --> 00:26:55,381
I'm not looking down on your profession.

312
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:58,544
I'm just curious. Is there a difference?

313
00:26:58,554 --> 00:27:00,416
♪Even if there's no one else up there♪

314
00:27:00,416 --> 00:27:03,492
♪I know full well♪

315
00:27:04,096 --> 00:27:06,238
♪It's still not me♪

316
00:27:06,238 --> 00:27:06,861
Well...

317
00:27:09,343 --> 00:27:10,644
There is.

318
00:27:13,703 --> 00:27:15,332
Usually, there's a big difference.

319
00:27:16,006 --> 00:27:16,958
It's just...

320
00:27:17,502 --> 00:27:19,512
This time I took it as a side gig.

321
00:27:21,192 --> 00:27:24,140
The reason is pretty common.
I just needed the money.

322
00:27:25,754 --> 00:27:31,341
♪Just being the last one whom you look at♪

323
00:27:31,616 --> 00:27:32,320
So,

324
00:27:33,726 --> 00:27:35,785
how did you find me today anyway?

325
00:27:36,383 --> 00:27:37,742
It's classified information.

326
00:27:37,786 --> 00:27:40,864
♪More than I dreamed of♪

327
00:27:42,298 --> 00:27:42,851
Oh.

328
00:27:50,670 --> 00:27:53,644
And why did you become a cop?

329
00:27:56,431 --> 00:27:57,504
Nothing special.

330
00:27:57,504 --> 00:28:01,091
♪Someone is standing there♪

331
00:28:01,351 --> 00:28:04,776
♪Right there up in your stars♪

332
00:28:05,226 --> 00:28:09,060
♪Even if there's no one else up there♪

333
00:28:09,382 --> 00:28:12,908
♪I know full well♪

334
00:28:13,498 --> 00:28:15,072
♪It's still not me♪

335
00:28:17,594 --> 00:28:20,352
♪Just being the last one♪

336
00:28:20,352 --> 00:28:22,911
Um, Officer?
Could I ask for one more favor?

337
00:28:22,911 --> 00:28:26,490
♪Standing where I never should have been♪

338
00:28:26,490 --> 00:28:29,120
Could you roll down the window?
I'm feeling dizzy.

339
00:28:35,002 --> 00:28:39,788
♪Just being the last one whom you look at♪

340
00:28:40,032 --> 00:28:43,967
♪To be in your cold gaze♪

341
00:28:52,954 --> 00:28:58,290
♪Just being here, beneath the stars♪

342
00:28:59,616 --> 00:29:01,920
♪I'm so happy♪

343
00:29:13,184 --> 00:29:14,176
You okay?

344
00:29:14,490 --> 00:29:16,698
Much better. Thanks.

345
00:29:34,014 --> 00:29:35,328
Thank you so much, Officer.

346
00:29:47,479 --> 00:29:52,167
Sorry, but can I bother you one last time?
Can I borrow your phone? I need to call my mom.

347
00:29:56,992 --> 00:29:57,632
Thanks.

348
00:30:05,882 --> 00:30:08,655
Hey! Don't call yet!
I'm in the middle of a Live Sale!

349
00:30:09,060 --> 00:30:10,688
How do I hang this up?

350
00:30:11,578 --> 00:30:12,704
- Oh.
- Mom!

351
00:30:13,818 --> 00:30:15,117
Where's Singto?

352
00:30:15,924 --> 00:30:17,136
He's sleeping in the house.

353
00:30:18,042 --> 00:30:18,592
Oh, my!

354
00:30:18,874 --> 00:30:21,056
I missed it!

355
00:30:21,056 --> 00:30:23,798
Mom! Why did you leave Singto alone?

356
00:30:24,397 --> 00:30:26,688
How can know I where you are?

357
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:28,896
I was hungry, so I went out to eat!

358
00:30:29,530 --> 00:30:30,095
Here!

359
00:30:30,897 --> 00:30:33,114
Do you know who I'm with?
This is a police officer!

360
00:30:33,984 --> 00:30:35,756
I'll have him arrest you!

361
00:30:42,906 --> 00:30:43,535
Ugh!

362
00:30:43,972 --> 00:30:46,493
What is Singto doing?

363
00:30:57,824 --> 00:30:58,572
I'm so sorry about that.

364
00:30:59,304 --> 00:31:00,568
Thanks again.

365
00:31:01,114 --> 00:31:02,517
And sorry again.

366
00:31:02,976 --> 00:31:04,800
You had to see us bickering

367
00:31:04,986 --> 00:31:05,829
on such a tiring day.

368
00:31:08,393 --> 00:31:09,663
I'm used to seeing it.

369
00:31:11,898 --> 00:31:12,480
Right.

370
00:31:14,330 --> 00:31:15,008
Well...

371
00:31:16,288 --> 00:31:17,806
It was nice meeting you, Officer.

372
00:31:18,947 --> 00:31:19,616
I hope

373
00:31:19,904 --> 00:31:21,394
we have the chance to meet again.

374
00:31:22,464 --> 00:31:23,413
Nice to meet you, too.

375
00:31:25,338 --> 00:31:26,598
But next time we meet,

376
00:31:27,008 --> 00:31:29,396
I hope it's not
as an officer and a suspect.

377
00:31:31,322 --> 00:31:33,026
If you really don't want to get arrested,

378
00:31:34,037 --> 00:31:35,504
stay away from the illegal trade, okay?

379
00:31:39,584 --> 00:31:40,224
I will.

380
00:31:41,818 --> 00:31:42,551
Thank you.

381
00:31:43,402 --> 00:31:44,263
Go inside.

382
00:31:48,288 --> 00:31:49,919
There, there.

383
00:31:51,834 --> 00:31:54,944
Don't cry.

384
00:31:54,944 --> 00:31:55,648
Did you transfer it yet?

385
00:31:56,672 --> 00:31:58,251
Not yet, Mom.

386
00:31:58,385 --> 00:31:59,840
Mom.

387
00:32:00,314 --> 00:32:01,806
You have to promise me.

388
00:32:01,882 --> 00:32:05,472
You'll save it. If you don't, no matter
how much I give you, it'll never be enough.

389
00:32:05,472 --> 00:32:06,624
I am saving!

390
00:32:06,624 --> 00:32:08,704
Otherwise, how would I have money
to get into a share savings scheme?

391
00:32:10,400 --> 00:32:12,928
Then how did you end up in so much debt?

392
00:32:13,050 --> 00:32:14,335
Mom.

393
00:32:14,522 --> 00:32:15,152
Ugh!

394
00:32:15,834 --> 00:32:18,351
- I'm hot. I'm going to take a shower!
- Mom, I'm tired of saying this.

395
00:32:18,746 --> 00:32:21,760
- Let's go to sleep.
- Mom.

396
00:32:22,144 --> 00:32:24,117
Okay, let's go to sleep.

397
00:32:34,816 --> 00:32:36,631
I'll transfer the 40,000 baht to you.

398
00:32:37,056 --> 00:32:40,259
See? You can earn money if you really try.

399
00:32:44,928 --> 00:32:45,858
Mom.

400
00:32:46,426 --> 00:32:47,584
In this industry,

401
00:32:47,840 --> 00:32:49,855
I don't even know how much longer
I can keep earning like this.

402
00:32:50,618 --> 00:32:51,325
Come on.

403
00:32:51,808 --> 00:32:53,689
I watched a clip the other day.

404
00:32:53,689 --> 00:32:54,464
It said that

405
00:32:54,464 --> 00:32:56,008
don't be afraid of being embarrassed.

406
00:32:56,250 --> 00:32:57,769
People aren't born equal.

407
00:32:57,902 --> 00:33:01,154
We are not all born
with the same advantages.

408
00:33:01,154 --> 00:33:03,250
You were born handsome.

409
00:33:03,386 --> 00:33:07,232
You have to use that to your advantage.
Why bother with architecture?

410
00:33:07,688 --> 00:33:13,054
Staying up all night, who knows if you'll
even make this much when you graduate?

411
00:33:15,162 --> 00:33:16,960
I'm fine with it.

412
00:33:17,722 --> 00:33:18,310
Hmm?

413
00:33:19,098 --> 00:33:20,035
Oh, Mom.

414
00:33:21,216 --> 00:33:24,288
I don't care what people think
or if they gossip about me.

415
00:33:24,954 --> 00:33:27,545
I'm just worried about
when my liver is going to give out.

416
00:33:31,758 --> 00:33:32,545
Mom.

417
00:33:33,952 --> 00:33:35,439
I'm serious.

418
00:33:35,978 --> 00:33:37,400
You really need to start saving.

419
00:33:38,048 --> 00:33:40,213
Besides, Singto still isn't talking yet.

420
00:33:41,050 --> 00:33:43,060
We have to take him to see a doctor.

421
00:33:44,218 --> 00:33:44,861
Yeah.

422
00:33:45,370 --> 00:33:46,369
I get it.

423
00:33:47,872 --> 00:33:51,342
Just buy a frog to hit its mouth.
No need to see a doctor. Saves us a lot of money.

424
00:33:52,218 --> 00:33:54,101
Oh, Mom!

425
00:33:55,602 --> 00:33:57,888
That's your grandson.
Don't you worry about him at all?

426
00:33:57,888 --> 00:34:00,128
Well, tell Wai to pay for it herself then.

427
00:34:00,826 --> 00:34:01,664
He's her kid.

428
00:34:02,176 --> 00:34:04,320
You reap what you sow.

429
00:34:04,730 --> 00:34:06,713
My money is my money.

430
00:34:09,440 --> 00:34:11,120
Time to take the righteous path,
right, Mom?

431
00:34:25,722 --> 00:34:27,285
Sky, you bad guy!

432
00:34:27,584 --> 00:34:28,754
Why didn't you tell me everything?

433
00:34:29,498 --> 00:34:31,368
What? I've told you everything.

434
00:34:31,418 --> 00:34:32,320
Everything?

435
00:34:33,114 --> 00:34:35,648
That guy wanted an extreme service.
Why didn't you mention it?

436
00:34:35,898 --> 00:34:38,016
I told you what I heard.

437
00:34:38,016 --> 00:34:39,264
What now?

438
00:34:39,264 --> 00:34:40,571
You don't even look sorry.

439
00:34:40,762 --> 00:34:44,149
Wayu's head got busted
because of your weird client.

440
00:34:51,034 --> 00:34:51,859
Hey!

441
00:34:53,210 --> 00:34:55,296
How was I supposed to know?

442
00:34:56,154 --> 00:34:57,630
- You didn't know?
- Hey!

443
00:34:57,690 --> 00:34:58,880
- That was your regular client.
- Hey!

444
00:34:59,098 --> 00:35:00,687
Normally, you're stingy.
Why did you share all of a sudden?

445
00:35:00,687 --> 00:35:02,848
- Stop it!
- Tai.

446
00:35:02,848 --> 00:35:04,050
- Did you set him up on purpose?
- Tai, calm down.

447
00:35:04,058 --> 00:35:05,099
Just calm down.

448
00:35:05,370 --> 00:35:06,496
It's not worth getting into trouble.

449
00:35:07,098 --> 00:35:07,744
Hold on.

450
00:35:08,506 --> 00:35:09,155
Fine.

451
00:35:09,888 --> 00:35:11,232
Think whatever you want.

452
00:35:12,104 --> 00:35:14,434
I even shared my client with you.

453
00:35:15,764 --> 00:35:16,757
Darn it!

454
00:35:16,960 --> 00:35:17,984
Kids these days.

455
00:35:18,618 --> 00:35:20,107
They have no idea what "gratitude" means.

456
00:35:20,282 --> 00:35:21,262
You're right, Sky.

457
00:35:23,034 --> 00:35:24,032
Oh.

458
00:35:25,050 --> 00:35:25,888
I get it now.

459
00:35:27,098 --> 00:35:29,493
The reason you got your head busted

460
00:35:30,170 --> 00:35:31,239
wasn't because of the client.

461
00:35:32,346 --> 00:35:34,516
It's because you are bad at your job.

462
00:35:35,328 --> 00:35:35,968
Sky, you wretch!

463
00:35:37,146 --> 00:35:38,944
- What?
- Hey!

464
00:35:40,762 --> 00:35:42,656
Oh, my! Not the face!

465
00:35:42,656 --> 00:35:46,161
- My face cost a fortune!
- Bring it on!

466
00:35:46,161 --> 00:35:48,302
- I told you to calm down!
- Fight me!

467
00:35:48,410 --> 00:35:49,376
Who is that?

468
00:35:49,626 --> 00:35:50,343
It's me.

469
00:35:50,682 --> 00:35:51,452
What are you going to do about it?

470
00:35:55,514 --> 00:35:57,010
I've said this before, haven't I?

471
00:35:57,658 --> 00:35:59,194
(First one to swing
is fined 5,000 Baht or fired)

472
00:36:00,122 --> 00:36:00,831
Speak up.

473
00:36:03,055 --> 00:36:07,936
- "First one to swing is fined 5,000 Baht or fired."
- "First one to swing is fined 5,000 Baht or fired."

474
00:36:08,346 --> 00:36:09,136
Louder!

475
00:36:10,106 --> 00:36:14,504
- "First one to swing is fined 5,000 Baht or fired."
- "First one to swing is fined 5,000 Baht or fired."

476
00:36:15,819 --> 00:36:17,646
But Sky messed with Wayu first!

477
00:36:18,848 --> 00:36:22,464
Messed with him? Where's your proof?

478
00:36:23,258 --> 00:36:24,991
I have my proof.

479
00:36:26,671 --> 00:36:30,508
Foei, I have a show tomorrow!
What am I supposed to do?

480
00:36:31,232 --> 00:36:32,606
It hurts!

481
00:36:33,336 --> 00:36:35,286
Wayu. Tai.

482
00:36:35,648 --> 00:36:36,640
To the black room.

483
00:36:55,130 --> 00:36:56,679
Anything else you want to say to me?

484
00:37:02,112 --> 00:37:03,034
No, that's all.

485
00:37:06,944 --> 00:37:08,722
I must lock you.

486
00:37:09,946 --> 00:37:12,074
Even if Sky was wrong
for giving you that job.

487
00:37:13,938 --> 00:37:15,716
In the end, Wayu, you accepted it.

488
00:37:16,472 --> 00:37:17,719
You have to take responsibility
for that choice.

489
00:37:18,531 --> 00:37:19,556
Understand?

490
00:37:29,050 --> 00:37:30,083
Today,

491
00:37:34,911 --> 00:37:36,324
no one is getting fired.

492
00:37:41,856 --> 00:37:44,463
I'm not stupid enough
to fire our second-best.

493
00:37:46,298 --> 00:37:47,488
- Thank you so much, Foei.
- Thank you very much.

494
00:37:47,520 --> 00:37:48,544
Thank you.

495
00:37:49,152 --> 00:37:52,086
But I'm taking half a month
of Tai's earnings

496
00:37:52,954 --> 00:37:54,457
to cover Sky's face treatment.

497
00:37:55,947 --> 00:37:59,526
As for Wayu,
you're suspended for three days

498
00:37:59,526 --> 00:38:01,888
until that wound on your head is healed.

499
00:38:04,657 --> 00:38:05,889
Thank you, Foei.

500
00:38:11,861 --> 00:38:12,778
Tai.

501
00:38:14,458 --> 00:38:15,513
I'm sorry.

502
00:38:15,680 --> 00:38:17,224
I dragged you into trouble.

503
00:38:17,338 --> 00:38:18,816
Hey, forget about it.

504
00:38:19,578 --> 00:38:21,562
We're friends, man.

505
00:38:21,987 --> 00:38:23,735
Friends should protect each other.

506
00:38:25,080 --> 00:38:25,777
Come on.

507
00:38:26,528 --> 00:38:28,370
You aren't in this alone.

508
00:38:31,168 --> 00:38:33,888
Besides, I've wanted to punch
that guy for a long time.

509
00:38:34,875 --> 00:38:37,024
I don't care how much it costs me.

510
00:38:37,754 --> 00:38:38,661
Bad guy!

511
00:38:39,338 --> 00:38:40,522
Right on the chin!

512
00:38:41,818 --> 00:38:42,354
Honestly,

513
00:38:42,874 --> 00:38:43,923
did my punch look good?

514
00:38:45,978 --> 00:38:46,672
Pretty good.

515
00:38:47,546 --> 00:38:49,472
Boom! Upper-cut!

516
00:38:50,010 --> 00:38:52,131
Hmph, what a shame.

517
00:39:14,010 --> 00:39:21,626
(Deleting work schedule for
today, tomorrow, the day after)

518
00:39:45,295 --> 00:39:46,222
Hello?

519
00:39:46,599 --> 00:39:50,425
I'm actually free tonight.
Can I work at your place?

520
00:39:51,641 --> 00:39:53,491
Oh, I can just wait tables.

521
00:39:55,008 --> 00:39:58,884
Perfect. I'll be there tomorrow at 6 PM.

522
00:40:00,771 --> 00:40:02,259
Thank you so much. Thanks.

523
00:40:11,226 --> 00:40:24,826
(Pay the utility bills, Go to work at Moonlit
Last day of suspension of schooling)

524
00:41:22,650 --> 00:41:25,522
Hey, is it done yet?
The deadline is tomorrow!

525
00:41:26,029 --> 00:41:27,968
All you do is sleep.

526
00:41:27,968 --> 00:41:29,356
Your mom is looking for you!

527
00:41:29,773 --> 00:41:32,448
- Let me sit.
- Just sleep a bit.

528
00:41:32,448 --> 00:41:34,560
- Sleep or work?
- Fine, work.

529
00:41:36,473 --> 00:41:37,600
How much is left?

530
00:41:37,818 --> 00:41:38,688
Quite a lot.

531
00:41:40,122 --> 00:41:41,571
Here. Let me handle it.

532
00:41:42,394 --> 00:41:43,245
Good.

533
00:42:03,674 --> 00:42:11,434
(Post a building photo)

534
00:42:30,140 --> 00:42:34,045
Are you sure about withdrawing again?
You're so close to graduating.

535
00:42:36,058 --> 00:42:37,435
Yes. I'm sure.

536
00:42:38,144 --> 00:42:39,698
Alright. I'll need your documents, then.

537
00:42:41,460 --> 00:42:42,496
Thank you.

538
00:43:03,450 --> 00:43:04,537
Thank you.

539
00:43:05,344 --> 00:43:06,340
You're welcome.

540
00:43:08,154 --> 00:43:10,624
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine. Bye.

541
00:43:38,298 --> 00:43:39,850
How is it, buddy?

542
00:43:40,058 --> 00:43:42,368
One-year membership.

543
00:43:42,554 --> 00:43:45,024
- This is so fancy.
- Haha.

544
00:43:45,210 --> 00:43:48,288
Right? I've got all problems cleared.

545
00:43:49,242 --> 00:43:52,210
- Come on! Get on!
- I'm not so sure about this.

546
00:43:52,826 --> 00:43:54,752
- Trust me, man! If you use this thing,
- Right.

547
00:43:54,752 --> 00:43:58,304
you'll have the stamina to run back
and forth to Pratunam over ten times!

548
00:43:58,304 --> 00:44:00,320
Grip the handles tight.

549
00:44:00,538 --> 00:44:03,041
- Your legs!
- Yeah.

550
00:44:03,354 --> 00:44:08,480
There you go. Keep your legs tense!

551
00:44:15,354 --> 00:44:16,064
Tai.

552
00:44:16,506 --> 00:44:17,044
Hmm?

553
00:44:17,440 --> 00:44:18,740
I officially withdrew
from my classes today.

554
00:44:20,780 --> 00:44:22,173
Yeah. Fine.

555
00:44:23,171 --> 00:44:24,224
But don't give up, okay?

556
00:44:24,793 --> 00:44:25,824
Just save up for now.

557
00:44:26,329 --> 00:44:27,179
Save up with me.

558
00:44:28,362 --> 00:44:29,677
What are you saving up for anyway?

559
00:44:30,528 --> 00:44:31,548
Getting married?

560
00:44:32,512 --> 00:44:33,927
Saving up for my car.

561
00:44:34,483 --> 00:44:36,864
My car needs new shock absorbers.

562
00:44:38,976 --> 00:44:40,561
So that's why you're training this hard?

563
00:44:41,907 --> 00:44:45,039
Well, I have to go shirtless tonight.
Since you're suspended,

564
00:44:45,039 --> 00:44:46,871
it's my time to rake in the tips!

565
00:44:49,343 --> 00:44:50,566
Ugh!

566
00:44:51,073 --> 00:44:53,332
Are you training for the Olympics
or something?

567
00:44:53,332 --> 00:44:54,012
Haha.

568
00:44:54,181 --> 00:44:55,998
Stop! Don't distract me.

569
00:44:56,576 --> 00:44:57,424
Ugh.

570
00:44:57,888 --> 00:44:59,488
Whatever you say.

571
00:45:00,096 --> 00:45:00,800
I'm done.

572
00:45:01,312 --> 00:45:02,713
I'm going to hit the sauna first.

573
00:45:03,360 --> 00:45:04,488
Go ahead.

574
00:45:04,488 --> 00:45:05,280
See you.

575
00:45:06,464 --> 00:45:07,450
Ah!

576
00:45:20,192 --> 00:45:21,062
Oh, Officer!

577
00:45:23,840 --> 00:45:25,994
What a coincidence.
Do you work out here, too?

578
00:45:28,960 --> 00:45:29,645
Yes.

579
00:45:30,624 --> 00:45:31,448
You too?

580
00:45:32,435 --> 00:45:33,037
Well,

581
00:45:33,384 --> 00:45:34,621
something like that.

582
00:45:38,816 --> 00:45:39,633
Excuse me?

583
00:45:40,226 --> 00:45:40,898
Yes?

584
00:45:41,517 --> 00:45:42,919
Could you help me apply some body oil?

585
00:45:52,704 --> 00:45:56,768
I'm not really available.

586
00:46:40,832 --> 00:46:42,026
Do you want to get arrested again?

587
00:46:45,152 --> 00:46:46,432
Arrested for what, Officer?

588
00:47:00,608 --> 00:47:01,826
Go ahead and arrest me, then.

589
00:47:03,136 --> 00:47:04,270
By the way,

590
00:47:05,307 --> 00:47:08,064
what exactly would
the charges be this time?

591
00:47:12,544 --> 00:47:13,670
Or...

592
00:47:14,390 --> 00:47:16,475
Are you interested in my 'services'?

593
00:47:18,688 --> 00:47:19,517
No.

594
00:47:36,483 --> 00:47:38,994
Well, if you ever change your mind,

595
00:47:40,086 --> 00:47:41,609
you can always find me at the club.

596
00:48:16,861 --> 00:48:18,332
Why are you looking at me like that?

597
00:48:19,840 --> 00:48:20,876
Hmm?

598
00:48:22,208 --> 00:48:23,939
I haven't done anything wrong.

599
00:48:26,558 --> 00:48:27,344
Or...

600
00:48:28,943 --> 00:48:30,399
Do you want to check for yourself

601
00:48:32,425 --> 00:48:33,227
to see if I'm hiding

602
00:48:34,359 --> 00:48:36,192
anything illegal?

603
00:49:14,049 --> 00:49:15,745
See you around, Officer.

604
00:49:42,620 --> 00:49:43,200
Yes.

605
00:49:45,773 --> 00:49:47,604
Are you getting involved with
that Soi 2 case?

606
00:49:48,514 --> 00:49:49,815
It's a case I'm responsible for.

607
00:49:51,296 --> 00:49:52,472
You won't get promoted
doing stuff like this.

608
00:49:52,978 --> 00:49:54,958
If you want to move up, listen to me.

609
00:49:56,105 --> 00:49:57,377
Take this case instead.

610
00:50:03,195 --> 00:50:04,403
I can't take on any more cases.

611
00:50:05,452 --> 00:50:06,298
Besides,

612
00:50:06,656 --> 00:50:07,527
the Soi 2 case

613
00:50:07,872 --> 00:50:09,308
will lead to something much bigger.

614
00:50:10,115 --> 00:50:11,397
I'm seeing it through.

615
00:50:12,196 --> 00:50:14,506
- But you should...
- I have a date with Rose.

616
00:50:15,432 --> 00:50:17,158
If there's nothing else, I'll be going.

617
00:50:19,772 --> 00:50:20,192
Fine, go.

618
00:50:21,920 --> 00:50:23,022
See you at home, Dad.

619
00:50:23,843 --> 00:50:24,674
Well,

620
00:50:25,184 --> 00:50:26,290
this week,

621
00:50:27,111 --> 00:50:29,132
invite Rose for dinner.

622
00:50:30,256 --> 00:50:31,834
I want to discuss
important matters with her.

623
00:50:35,392 --> 00:50:36,190
Understood.

624
00:50:44,192 --> 00:50:46,198
Sir, shall I serve the wine now?

625
00:50:46,998 --> 00:50:48,056
Not yet.

626
00:50:55,599 --> 00:50:59,232
Babe, I'm on my way. Wait for me.

627
00:50:59,232 --> 00:51:00,416
I see.

628
00:51:01,408 --> 00:51:02,560
Should I order something for you?

629
00:51:02,560 --> 00:51:04,648
No, it's okay.
I just had some instant noodles.

630
00:51:06,210 --> 00:51:07,735
Alright then.

631
00:51:22,880 --> 00:51:24,209
Oh, Officer!

632
00:51:29,408 --> 00:51:31,776
There you go again.

633
00:51:33,069 --> 00:51:34,521
Looking at me like a suspect.

634
00:51:35,456 --> 00:51:37,883
I came here to do a part-time job. I didn't
come here to take on that kind of work.

635
00:51:39,408 --> 00:51:40,886
I didn't say anything.

636
00:51:42,041 --> 00:51:43,654
I'm just here for dinner,

637
00:51:44,526 --> 00:51:45,737
not for an investigation.

638
00:51:46,880 --> 00:51:48,480
Good to know.

639
00:51:49,376 --> 00:51:52,544
You're always staring at me.

640
00:51:53,820 --> 00:51:55,342
It's making me nervous.

641
00:51:57,568 --> 00:52:01,617
Is something wrong?
Or do you think I followed you here?

642
00:52:02,912 --> 00:52:05,280
No. I was just lost in thought.

643
00:52:05,888 --> 00:52:06,941
Okay.

644
00:52:07,360 --> 00:52:10,016
Wayu! Can you help
with some foreign customers?

645
00:52:10,016 --> 00:52:11,241
Sure, I'm coming.

646
00:52:14,062 --> 00:52:16,424
Excuse me, Officer.

647
00:52:17,248 --> 00:52:19,344
I have to go back to my "honest work" now.

648
00:52:20,028 --> 00:52:20,796
Please, go ahead.

649
00:52:49,472 --> 00:52:54,368
(Rose: Something came up at home.
I can't make it tonight)

650
00:52:59,200 --> 00:52:59,942
Excuse me.

651
00:53:00,768 --> 00:53:01,863
Check, please.

652
00:53:04,585 --> 00:53:06,404
Hello, mind if I join you?

653
00:53:09,482 --> 00:53:11,168
Are you here alone?

654
00:53:11,648 --> 00:53:12,918
I was supposed to meet a friend.

655
00:53:13,632 --> 00:53:14,907
She couldn't make it.

656
00:53:17,280 --> 00:53:18,620
That's too bad.

657
00:53:19,674 --> 00:53:20,956
Want to go somewhere else?

658
00:53:22,496 --> 00:53:24,805
No, thanks. I'm heading home.

659
00:53:25,920 --> 00:53:26,818
Come on.

660
00:53:29,216 --> 00:53:30,822
My place is just around the corner.

661
00:53:31,968 --> 00:53:33,358
You'd better let me go.

662
00:53:33,984 --> 00:53:34,867
I'm in a hurry.

663
00:53:36,640 --> 00:53:38,039
Babe!

664
00:53:38,969 --> 00:53:39,776
Babe!

665
00:53:40,352 --> 00:53:41,804
Babe, whose hand are you holding?

666
00:53:44,096 --> 00:53:45,455
Babe, are you cheating on me?

667
00:53:48,732 --> 00:53:49,728
He grabbed me first.

668
00:53:50,336 --> 00:53:52,479
Babe, what does he have that I don't?

669
00:53:52,479 --> 00:53:54,147
Answer me!

670
00:53:56,608 --> 00:53:58,627
Are you calling me ugly?

671
00:53:58,720 --> 00:53:59,968
I didn't say that!

672
00:54:00,188 --> 00:54:00,910
That's enough.

673
00:54:02,982 --> 00:54:03,488
(Investigation)

674
00:54:04,154 --> 00:54:05,121
I'm a police officer.

675
00:54:05,821 --> 00:54:08,960
If this turns into an assault,
I will have to arrest you.

676
00:54:10,368 --> 00:54:11,185
Police?

677
00:54:14,208 --> 00:54:16,106
Okay, Officer!

678
00:54:17,507 --> 00:54:19,122
Check, please!

679
00:54:29,534 --> 00:54:30,345
Are you hurt?

680
00:54:31,217 --> 00:54:32,192
I'm fine.

681
00:54:32,350 --> 00:54:33,303
Well...

682
00:54:34,464 --> 00:54:35,455
Do you have a change of clothes?

683
00:54:38,189 --> 00:54:40,127
No, but it's okay.

684
00:54:40,704 --> 00:54:43,840
Fine. I'll check the backroom.
They might have something.

685
00:54:44,896 --> 00:54:45,743
Come on.

686
00:54:53,689 --> 00:54:54,823
Officer.

687
00:54:55,340 --> 00:54:56,381
It's fine.

688
00:55:04,800 --> 00:55:05,994
I just want to thank you

689
00:55:06,368 --> 00:55:07,538
for helping me back then.

690
00:55:09,312 --> 00:55:10,593
Thank you very much.

691
00:55:10,987 --> 00:55:13,816
Actually, just the fact that
you'd lend me a jacket is plenty.

692
00:55:14,336 --> 00:55:15,457
Thank you very much indeed.

693
00:55:16,000 --> 00:55:16,900
Don't mention it.

694
00:55:20,128 --> 00:55:23,232
Wayu, help with the serving!

695
00:55:23,744 --> 00:55:25,536
Got it. I'm coming.

696
00:55:29,248 --> 00:55:31,713
Thanks. Well, I'll be going now.

697
00:55:48,480 --> 00:55:49,555
See you then.

698
00:56:03,712 --> 00:56:05,127
Oh, Officer!

699
00:56:11,488 --> 00:56:12,640
You're still here?

700
00:56:13,568 --> 00:56:15,425
I was just finishing
some work calls in the car.

701
00:56:16,544 --> 00:56:18,398
How are you getting home?

702
00:56:18,560 --> 00:56:20,949
I'll just catch a bus nearby.

703
00:56:22,841 --> 00:56:25,152
Aren't you afraid of
getting attacked again?

704
00:56:26,240 --> 00:56:27,705
Actually, I pass by your place.

705
00:56:28,416 --> 00:56:29,405
Want a ride?

706
00:56:29,536 --> 00:56:31,584
Oh, would that be okay?

707
00:56:32,128 --> 00:56:33,212
Well, thanks.

708
00:56:46,656 --> 00:56:47,705
Let's go.

709
00:56:56,096 --> 00:56:57,511
Okay. Drop me off right here.

710
00:57:10,720 --> 00:57:12,960
Do you usually listen to this song?

711
00:57:14,304 --> 00:57:17,144
I'm just listening to the same songs
on repeat, the same playlist.

712
00:57:18,080 --> 00:57:19,507
Hmm.

713
00:57:20,000 --> 00:57:21,143
Hmm.

714
00:57:21,839 --> 00:57:23,185
Since you work these hours,

715
00:57:23,737 --> 00:57:25,002
who looks after your kid?

716
00:57:25,474 --> 00:57:26,592
Ah.

717
00:57:27,360 --> 00:57:30,375
He's just my nephew.
I'm not that fast of a mover.

718
00:57:32,583 --> 00:57:34,783
And during the day?

719
00:57:35,999 --> 00:57:36,701
Well,

720
00:57:37,313 --> 00:57:39,859
I drop him off at daycare.

721
00:57:39,859 --> 00:57:41,731
That's why I have to hustle for work.

722
00:57:41,819 --> 00:57:43,872
He's at that age where he's growing fast.

723
00:57:44,948 --> 00:57:46,394
Doesn't your mom help?

724
00:57:48,263 --> 00:57:49,685
Well,

725
00:57:50,180 --> 00:57:51,968
she isn't really fond of childcare.

726
00:57:52,551 --> 00:57:53,657
So it means

727
00:57:54,172 --> 00:57:55,705
you're providing
for the whole family on your own?

728
00:57:56,864 --> 00:57:57,421
Yeah.

729
00:57:57,792 --> 00:58:01,737
So I just have to keep hustling for gigs,
taking whatever I can get. I need the cash.

730
00:58:04,901 --> 00:58:05,823
You're impressive.

731
00:58:11,790 --> 00:58:12,655
What was that?

732
00:58:13,152 --> 00:58:14,294
I mean

733
00:58:16,005 --> 00:58:16,913
you're doing a great job.

734
00:58:18,070 --> 00:58:19,946
Taking care of your family
all by yourself like this.

735
00:58:25,480 --> 00:58:26,359
Thank you.

736
00:58:29,358 --> 00:58:31,218
If you ever need help, let me know.

737
00:58:32,416 --> 00:58:33,690
Just as long as it's nothing illegal.

738
00:58:42,741 --> 00:58:45,355
Well, thanks for the ride.

739
00:58:45,920 --> 00:58:47,001
I guess

740
00:58:47,314 --> 00:58:49,984
the taxes I paid
are finally worth it today.

741
00:58:51,776 --> 00:58:53,063
This is my own gas money.

742
00:58:53,930 --> 00:58:54,875
Not taxpayer money.

743
00:58:55,200 --> 00:58:56,669
I was just kidding.

744
00:59:11,528 --> 00:59:15,059
Oh, I'll wash this jacket

745
00:59:15,585 --> 00:59:16,705
and return it to you.

746
00:59:17,854 --> 00:59:18,824
It's fine.

747
00:59:19,578 --> 00:59:20,723
No, It's fine.

748
00:59:20,723 --> 00:59:23,075
I'll wash it until it smells great.

749
00:59:23,360 --> 00:59:26,786
And, once you're home,
don't forget to let me know.

750
00:59:32,691 --> 00:59:33,920
Bye-bye!

751
00:59:36,416 --> 00:59:37,760
- Bye-bye.
- Yes.

752
00:59:46,336 --> 00:59:47,291
Sigh.

753
00:59:47,291 --> 00:59:50,464
♪Just being the last one
whom you think of♪

754
00:59:50,464 --> 00:59:54,368
♪Standing where I never should have been♪

755
00:59:54,368 --> 01:00:00,960
♪And honestly, that's enough for me♪

756
01:00:03,168 --> 01:00:05,984
♪Just being the last one♪

757
01:00:05,984 --> 01:00:08,000
♪Whom you look at♪

758
01:00:08,000 --> 01:00:11,712
♪To be in your cold gaze♪

759
01:00:11,712 --> 01:00:18,433
♪Just this brings more happiness
than I dreamed of♪

760
01:00:20,448 --> 01:00:23,296
♪I'm just happy being right here♪

761
01:00:23,296 --> 01:00:24,076
Oh, no!

762
01:00:26,144 --> 01:00:27,519
I forgot to ask for his Line ID.

763
01:00:29,152 --> 01:00:30,361
Well.

764
01:01:14,976 --> 01:01:17,600
(Wayu: Have you arrived home yet?)

765
01:01:18,806 --> 01:01:21,698
You have to thank your mom
for getting his number.

766
01:01:22,304 --> 01:01:22,963
Yeah.

767
01:01:25,654 --> 01:01:30,313
Sorry, but can I bother you one last time?
Can I borrow your phone? I need to call my mom.

768
01:01:31,040 --> 01:01:32,034
Well,

769
01:01:32,812 --> 01:01:35,906
I sent him an SMS.
Is he going to think I'm a creep?

770
01:01:36,320 --> 01:01:38,784
I tried adding him on Line,
but nothing popped up.

771
01:01:38,976 --> 01:01:39,958
Don't sweat it.

772
01:01:39,959 --> 01:01:42,212
Let's just see how he feels.

773
01:01:43,954 --> 01:01:44,950
Yeah, okay.

774
01:01:51,456 --> 01:01:52,583
Wow.

775
01:02:14,304 --> 01:02:16,512
(SMS, Krit: I'm home)

776
01:02:39,552 --> 01:02:41,248
Sigh.

777
01:02:41,248 --> 01:02:43,168
My cooking is unmatched.

778
01:02:43,617 --> 01:02:44,768
Thank you.

779
01:02:44,768 --> 01:02:46,921
- Well, enjoy your meal.
- Still as delicious as ever!

780
01:02:47,008 --> 01:02:47,904
Hmm.

781
01:02:47,904 --> 01:02:49,022
It smells great.

782
01:02:49,824 --> 01:02:51,456
- Tai.
- Hmm?

783
01:02:52,096 --> 01:02:53,728
Do you think this means like?

784
01:02:54,816 --> 01:02:55,658
Who? Him or you?

785
01:02:56,096 --> 01:02:57,326
Him, obviously!

786
01:02:58,979 --> 01:03:00,530
I mean, there's a chance.

787
01:03:00,896 --> 01:03:02,420
But first,

788
01:03:02,420 --> 01:03:04,661
you need to check if he has a partner.

789
01:03:05,866 --> 01:03:07,943
Wow, look at you being a "good guy."

790
01:03:07,943 --> 01:03:10,877
It's not about being good.
It's about strategy.

791
01:03:10,877 --> 01:03:13,888
If he has one,
we'll know if he's worth stealing!

792
01:03:13,888 --> 01:03:15,176
Wow, you!

793
01:03:16,522 --> 01:03:17,440
Sigh.

794
01:03:17,440 --> 01:03:18,689
Look.

795
01:03:18,689 --> 01:03:20,832
Just ask him out again.

796
01:03:20,832 --> 01:03:22,496
Prove it one way or another.

797
01:03:23,264 --> 01:03:24,267
Otherwise,

798
01:03:24,275 --> 01:03:26,163
you'll just keep overthinking like this.

799
01:03:29,920 --> 01:03:30,905
Right?

800
01:03:31,720 --> 01:03:32,521
You want me

801
01:03:33,239 --> 01:03:35,215
to text him?

802
01:03:35,215 --> 01:03:38,016
No. Just go to
the Investigation Department

803
01:03:38,016 --> 01:03:40,493
or the station.

804
01:03:40,495 --> 01:03:42,967
You've got to make your move in person.

805
01:03:45,504 --> 01:03:47,552
Is our Wayu finally going to be
"off the market"?

806
01:03:47,552 --> 01:03:49,552
Hey! It's nothing like that.

807
01:03:49,552 --> 01:03:51,520
It's just a cop hitting on him.

808
01:03:51,520 --> 01:03:52,612
- Wow.
- Yeah.

809
01:03:52,612 --> 01:03:54,080
Let me give you some advice.

810
01:03:54,322 --> 01:03:55,209
Listen.

811
01:03:55,840 --> 01:03:59,040
Cops aren't all that great.
Don't lose your heart to them.

812
01:03:59,200 --> 01:04:01,239
The girls in Soi 2 have suffered enough.

813
01:04:01,824 --> 01:04:03,481
Stay single like this. It's better.

814
01:04:04,064 --> 01:04:05,243
Thanks.

815
01:04:07,216 --> 01:04:10,843
It's all about the strategy. Trust me.

816
01:04:10,843 --> 01:04:12,348
There are plenty of good cops out there.

817
01:04:13,276 --> 01:04:14,289
Hang on a sec.

818
01:04:23,424 --> 01:04:25,608
- Oh, my!
